NasusQ.name: Siphoning Strike
NasusQ.description: Nasus strikes his foe, dealing damage and increasing the power of his future Siphoning Strikes if he slays his target.

NasusW.name: Wither
NasusW.description: Nasus ages an enemy champion, decelerating their Move Speed and Attack Speed over time.

NasusE.name: Spirit Fire
NasusE.description: Nasus unleashes a spirit flame at a location, dealing damage and reducing the Armor of enemies who stand on it.

NasusR.name: Fury of the Sands
NasusR.description: Nasus unleashes a mighty sandstorm that batters nearby enemies. While the storm rages, he gains increased Health, Attack Range, damages nearby enemies, has a reduced cooldown on Siphoning Strike, and gains bonus Armor and Magic Resistance.

NautilusAnchorDrag.name: Dredge Line
NautilusAnchorDrag.description: Nautilus hurls his anchor forward.  Colliding with an enemy pulls them and Nautilus together, dealing magic damage.  Colliding with terrain pulls Nautilus towards it.

NautilusPiercingGaze.name: Titan's Wrath
NautilusPiercingGaze.description: Nautilus gains a temporary Shield.  While it persists, his Attacks deal damage over time to his target and surrounding enemies.

NautilusSplashZone.name: Riptide
NautilusSplashZone.description: Nautilus creates three exploding waves around himself. Each explosion damages and slows enemies.

NautilusGrandLine.name: Depth Charge
NautilusGrandLine.description: Nautilus fires a shockwave into the earth that chases an opponent. This shockwave rips up the earth above it, knocking enemies into the air. When it reaches the opponent, the shockwave erupts, knocking his target into the air and stunning them.

NeekoQ.name: Blooming Burst
NeekoQ.description: Neeko throws a seed dealing magic damage. The seed blooms again on hitting champions or killing units.

NeekoW.name: Shapesplitter
NeekoW.description: Neeko passively deals bonus magic damage every third attack, briefly increasing her move speed. Neeko can activate to send a clone in a direction and recast to change the direction of the clone.

NeekoE.name: Tangle-Barbs
NeekoE.description: Neeko slings a tangle that damages and roots everything it passes through. If the tangle kills an enemy or passes through a champion, it becomes larger, faster, and roots for longer.

NeekoR.name: Pop Blossom
NeekoR.description: After a short preparation, Neeko leaps into the air, knocking up all nearby enemies. Upon landing, nearby enemies are damaged and stunned. The preparation is hidden if Neeko is disguised.

JavelinToss.name: Javelin Toss / Takedown
JavelinToss.description: In human form, Nidalee throws a spiked javelin at her target that gains damage as it flies.  As a cougar, her next attack will attempt to fatally wound her target, dealing more damage the less life they have.

Bushwhack.name: Bushwhack / Pounce
Bushwhack.description: In human form, Nidalee lays a trap for unwary opponents that, when sprung, damages and reveals its target. As a cougar, she jumps in a direction, dealing damage in an area where she lands.

PrimalSurge.name: Primal Surge / Swipe
PrimalSurge.description: In human form, Nidalee channels the spirit of the cougar to heal her allies and imbue them with Attack Speed for a short duration. As a cougar, she claws in a direction, dealing damage to enemies in front of her.

AspectOfTheCougar.name: Aspect Of The Cougar
AspectOfTheCougar.description: Nidalee transforms into a cougar, gaining new abilities.

NilahQ.name: Formless Blade
NilahQ.description: With a snap of her whip-blade, Nilah damages any enemies she hits in a straight line in her chosen direction. This action extends her attack range for a short duration.

NilahW.name: Jubilant Veil
NilahW.description: Nilah envelops herself in mist, increasing her movement speed and allowing her to gracefully dodge all incoming attacks. Any allies she touches during the mist's duration will also gain this effect.

NilahE.name: Slipstream
NilahE.description: Nilah enthusiastically dashes toward her target, dealing damage to any enemies she passes through on the way.

NilahR.name: Apotheosis
NilahR.description: Twirling her whip-blade in joyful exuberance, Nilah deals damage to enemies around her before pulling them closer with her weapon.

NocturneDuskbringer.name: Duskbringer
NocturneDuskbringer.description: Nocturne throws a shadow blade that deals damage, leaves a Dusk Trail, and causes champions to leave a Dusk Trail. While on the trail, Nocturne can move through units and has increased Move Speed and Attack Damage.

NocturneShroudofDarkness.name: Shroud of Darkness
NocturneShroudofDarkness.description: Nocturne empowers his blades, passively gaining Attack Speed. Activating Shroud of Darkness allows Nocturne to fade into the shadows, creating a magical barrier which blocks a single enemy ability and doubles his passive Attack Speed if successful.

NocturneUnspeakableHorror.name: Unspeakable Horror
NocturneUnspeakableHorror.description: Nocturne plants a nightmare into his target's mind, dealing damage each second and applying fear to the target if they do not get out of range by the end of the duration.

NocturneParanoia.name: Paranoia
NocturneParanoia.description: Nocturne reduces the sight radius of all enemy champions and removes their ally vision in the process. He can then launch himself at a nearby enemy champion.

NunuQ.name: Consume
NunuQ.description: Willump takes a bite out of a minion, monster, or enemy champion, dealing damage and healing himself.

NunuW.name: Biggest Snowball Ever!
NunuW.description: Willump creates a snowball that grows in size and speed as he rolls it.  The snowball damages and knocks up enemies.

NunuE.name: Snowball Barrage
NunuE.description: Nunu throws multiple snowballs that damage enemies.  When he's finished, Willump roots any champions or large monsters that were hit by a snowball.

NunuR.name: Absolute Zero
NunuR.description: Nunu & Willump create a powerful blizzard in an area that slows enemies and deals massive damage at the end.

OlafAxeThrowCast.name: Undertow
OlafAxeThrowCast.description: Olaf throws an axe into the ground at a target location, dealing damage to enemies it passes through and reducing their Armor and Move Speed. If Olaf picks up the axe, the ability's cooldown is reset.

OlafFrenziedStrikes.name: Tough It Out
OlafFrenziedStrikes.description: Olaf's Attack Speed is increased and he gains a Shield.

OlafRecklessStrike.name: Reckless Swing
OlafRecklessStrike.description: Olaf attacks with such force that it deals true damage to his target and himself, refunding the Health cost if he destroys the target.

OlafRagnarok.name: Ragnarok
OlafRagnarok.description: Olaf passively gains increased armor and magic resist. He can activate this ability to become immune to disables for as long as he keeps attacking.

OrianaIzunaCommand.name: Command: Attack
OrianaIzunaCommand.description: Orianna commands her Ball to fire toward a target location, dealing magic damage to targets along the way (deals less damage to subsequent targets). Her Ball remains at the target location after.

OrianaDissonanceCommand.name: Command: Dissonance
OrianaDissonanceCommand.description: Orianna commands her Ball to release a pulse of energy, dealing magic damage around it. This leaves a field behind that speeds up allies and slows enemies.

OrianaRedactCommand.name: Command: Protect
OrianaRedactCommand.description: Orianna commands her Ball to attach to an allied champion, Shielding them and dealing magic damage to any enemies it passes through on the way. Additionally, the Ball grants additional Armor and Magic Resist to the champion it is attached to.

OrianaDetonateCommand.name: Command: Shockwave
OrianaDetonateCommand.description: Orianna commands her Ball to unleash a shockwave, dealing magic damage and launching nearby enemies towards the Ball after a short delay.

OrnnQ.name: Volcanic Rupture
OrnnQ.description: Ornn slams the ground, sending out a fissure dealing damage and slowing enemies hit. After a small delay, a magma pillar forms at the end location.

OrnnW.name: Bellows Breath
OrnnW.description: Ornn advances, breathing fire. Enemies hit by the final gout of flame become Brittle.

OrnnE.name: Searing Charge
OrnnE.description: Ornn charges, dealing damage to enemies he passes through. If Ornn collides with terrain while charging, the impact creates a shockwave around him which deals damage and knocks up enemies.

OrnnR.name: Call of the Forge God
OrnnR.description: Ornn summons a massive elemental at a location which travels toward him with increasing speed. Enemies run over by the elemental take damage, are slowed and are made Brittle. Ornn can recast the ability to charge into the elemental, redirecting it in the direction he hits it, causing the elemental to affect any enemies it runs over to be knocked up, dealing the same damage and re-applying Brittle.

PantheonQ.name: Comet Spear
PantheonQ.description: Pantheon either thrusts his spear or throws his spear in the chosen direction.

PantheonW.name: Shield Vault
PantheonW.description: Pantheon dashes to a target, damaging and stunning them.

PantheonE.name: Aegis Assault
PantheonE.description: Pantheon sets his shield, becoming invulnerable to damage from the front and striking repeatedly with his spear.

PantheonR.name: Grand Starfall
PantheonR.description: Pantheon composes himself and then leaps into the air, landing at a chosen location as a comet.

PoppyQ.name: Hammer Shock
PoppyQ.description: Poppy swings her hammer, dealing damage and creating a zone that will slow enemies and explode after a delay.

PoppyW.name: Steadfast Presence
PoppyW.description: Poppy passively gains Armor and Magic Resist. This bonus increases when she is low on Health. Poppy can activate Steadfast Presence to gain Move Speed and stop enemy dashes around her. If a dash is stopped, the enemy is slowed and grounded.

PoppyE.name: Heroic Charge
PoppyE.description: Poppy dashes to the target and pushes it back. If the target is pushed into a wall, it is stunned.

PoppyR.name: Keeper's Verdict
PoppyR.description: Poppy channels a hammer strike that knocks enemies very far away.

PykeQ.name: Bone Skewer
PykeQ.description: Pyke either stabs an enemy in front of him or pulls an enemy towards him.

PykeW.name: Ghostwater Dive
PykeW.description: Pyke enters Camouflage and gains significant Move Speed that decays over time.

PykeE.name: Phantom Undertow
PykeE.description: Pyke dashes and leaves behind a phantom that will return to him, stunning enemy champions along its path.

PykeR.name: Death From Below
PykeR.description: Pyke blinks to and executes low health enemies, allowing him to cast this spell again and granting additional gold to an ally who assists.

QiyanaQ.name: Elemental Wrath / Edge of Ixtal
QiyanaQ.description: Qiyana swings her weapon, dealing damage with a bonus effect based on her element.

QiyanaW.name: Terrashape
QiyanaW.description: Qiyana dashes to a location and enchants her weapon with an element. Her attacks and abilities deal bonus damage while her weapon is enchanted.

QiyanaE.name: Audacity
QiyanaE.description: Qiyana dashes to an enemy, damaging them.

QiyanaR.name: Supreme Display of Talent
QiyanaR.description: Qiyana sends out a shockwave that detonates whatever elements she hits with it, stunning and damaging nearby enemies.

QuinnQ.name: Blinding Assault
QuinnQ.description: Quinn calls Valor to mark an enemy and hinder its vision before damaging all enemies in the immediate area.

QuinnW.name: Heightened Senses
QuinnW.description: Passively grants Quinn Attack Speed and Move Speed after she attacks a <font color='#FFF673'>Vulnerable</font> target. Activate to have Valor reveal a large area nearby.

QuinnE.name: Vault
QuinnE.description: Quinn dashes to an enemy, dealing physical damage and slowing the target's Move Speed. Upon reaching the target, she leaps off the target, briefly interrupting it, and lands near her maximum Attack Range away from the target.

QuinnR.name: Behind Enemy Lines
QuinnR.description: Quinn and Valor team up to fly around at great speed.  Ending the ability casts Skystrike, which deals damage to nearby enemies and marks champions as Vulnerable.

RakanQ.name: Gleaming Quill
RakanQ.description: Flings a magical feather that deals magic damage. Striking a champion or epic monster enables Rakan to heal his allies.

RakanW.name: Grand Entrance
RakanW.description: Dashes to a location, knocking up nearby enemies on arrival.

RakanE.name: Battle Dance
RakanE.description: Flies to an allied champion granting them a shield. Can be re-cast for free for a short duration.

RakanR.name: The Quickness
RakanR.description: Gains Move Speed, charming and dealing magic damage to enemies touched.

PowerBall.name: Powerball
PowerBall.description: Rammus accelerates in a ball towards his enemies, dealing damage and slowing targets affected by the impact.

DefensiveBallCurl.name: Defensive Ball Curl
DefensiveBallCurl.description: Rammus goes into a defensive formation, vastly increasing his Armor and Magic Resistance, and returning damage to enemies that attack him.

PuncturingTaunt.name: Frenzying Taunt
PuncturingTaunt.description: Rammus taunts an enemy champion or monster into a reckless assault against him.

Tremors2.name: Soaring Slam
Tremors2.description: Rammus hops into the air and slams down at a target area, dealing magic damage and slowing enemies. If cast while Rammus is in Powerball, Rammus knocks up enemies near the center as well.

RekSaiQ.name: Queen's Wrath / Prey Seeker
RekSaiQ.description:
Rek'Sai's next 3 basic attacks deal bonus Physical Damage to nearby enemies.

While Burrowed, Rek'Sai launches a burst of void-charged earth that damages and reveals enemies hit.

RekSaiW.name: Burrow / Un-burrow
RekSaiW.description:
Rek'Sai burrows into the ground, gaining new abilities and increased Move Speed. Her vision range is reduced and she cannot use basic attacks.

While Burrowed, Rek'Sai may cast Unburrow to knock up and damage nearby enemies.

RekSaiE.name: Furious Bite / Tunnel
RekSaiE.description:
Rek'Sai bites her target, dealing bonus damage if she has max Fury.

While Burrowed, Rek'Sai creates a re-usable, long lasting tunnel. Enemies can destroy it by standing on top of either entrance.

RekSaiR.name: Void Rush
RekSaiR.description: Rek'Sai passively marks targets by damaging them. She can activate this ability to become briefly untargetable and lunge at a marked target for heavy damage based on their maximum health.

RellQ.name: Shattering Strike
RellQ.description: Rell deals magic damage to units in a line, breaking their shields and stunning them.

RellW_Dismount.name: Ferromancy: Crash Down
RellW_Dismount.description:
Mounted: Rell Dismounts, crashing down in her armor, Knocking enemies up and gaining a large Shield. While dismounted, she gains Armor, Magic Resist, Attack Speed, and Attack Range, but is Slowed.

Dismounted: Rell forms her Mount, gaining a burst of speed and Knocking Up the next enemy she attacks.

RellE.name: Full Tilt
RellE.description:
Passive: Rell gains out of combat Move Speed.

Active: Rell and an ally gain ramping Move Speed, doubled toward enemies and each other. Her next Attack explodes, dealing magic damage.

RellR.name: Magnet Storm
RellR.description: Rell explodes in a magnetic fury, violently Pulling nearby enemies toward herself. Then Rell constantly Drags nearby enemies toward herself for a short while, dealing magic damage over time.

RenataQ.name: Handshake
RenataQ.description: Renata sends out a missile rooting the first enemy hit, and can recast the ability to throw the unit in a direction.

RenataW.name: Bailout
RenataW.description: Renata buffs an allied champion to fight harder, delaying their death and potentially saving them if they get a takedown.

RenataE.name: Loyalty Program
RenataE.description: Renata sends out a pair of chemtech missiles, shielding allies and damaging and slowing enemies hit.

RenataR.name: Hostile Takeover
RenataR.description: Renata sends out a wave of chemicals, causing any enemies hit to go Berserk.

RenektonCleave.name: Cull the Meek
RenektonCleave.description: Renekton swings his blade, dealing moderate physical damage to all targets around him, and heals for a small portion of the damage dealt. If he has more than 50 Fury, his damage and heal are increased.

RenektonPreExecute.name: Ruthless Predator
RenektonPreExecute.description: Renekton slashes his target twice, dealing moderate physical damage and stuns them for 0.75 seconds. If Renekton has more than 50 Fury, he slashes his target three times, destroying damage shields on the target, dealing high physical damage, and stunning them for 1.5 seconds.

RenektonSliceAndDice.name: Slice and Dice
RenektonSliceAndDice.description: Renekton dashes, dealing damage to units along the way. Empowered, Renekton deals bonus damage and reduces the Armor of units hit.

RenektonReignOfTheTyrant.name: Dominus
RenektonReignOfTheTyrant.description: Renekton transforms into the Tyrant form, gaining bonus Health and dealing damage to enemies around him. While in this form, Renekton gains Fury periodically.

RengarQ.name: Savagery
RengarQ.description:
Rengar's next Attack brutally stabs his target for bonus damage.

Ferocity effect: deals increased damage and grants Attack Speed.

RengarW.name: Battle Roar
RengarW.description:
Rengar lets out a battle roar, damaging enemies and healing for some of the recent damage he has taken.

Ferocity effect: additionally breaks crowd control effects.

RengarE.name: Bola Strike
RengarE.description:
Rengar throws a bola, slowing the first target hit for a short duration.

Ferocity effect: roots the target.

RengarR.name: Thrill of the Hunt
RengarR.description: Rengar's predatory instincts take over, <font color='#cd90ee'>Camouflaging</font> him and revealing the nearest enemy champion in a large radius around him. During Thrill of the Hunt, Rengar gains Move Speed and he can leap to the tracked enemy without being in brush, reducing their armor.

RivenTriCleave.name: Broken Wings
RivenTriCleave.description: Riven lashes out in a series of strikes. This ability can be reactivated three times in a short time frame with the third hit knocking back nearby enemies.

RivenMartyr.name: Ki Burst
RivenMartyr.description: Riven emits a Ki Burst, damaging and stunning nearby enemies.

RivenFeint.name: Valor
RivenFeint.description: Riven steps forward a short distance and blocks incoming damage.

RivenFengShuiEngine.name: Blade of the Exile
RivenFengShuiEngine.description: Riven empowers her keepsake weapon with energy, and gains Attack Damage and Range. During this time, she also gains the ability to use Wind Slash, a powerful ranged attack, once.

RumbleFlameThrower.name: Flamespitter
RumbleFlameThrower.description: Rumble torches opponents in front of him, dealing magic damage in a cone for 3 seconds. While in Danger Zone this damage is increased.

RumbleShield.name: Scrap Shield
RumbleShield.description: Rumble pulls up a shield, protecting him from damage and granting him a quick burst of speed. While in Danger Zone, the shield strength and speed bonus is increased.

RumbleGrenade.name: Electro Harpoon
RumbleGrenade.description: Rumble launches a harpoon, electrocuting his target with magic damage, slowing their Move Speed, and reducing their Magic Resist. Rumble can carry 2 harpoons at a time. While in Danger Zone the damage and slow percentage is increased.

RumbleCarpetBomb.name: The Equalizer
RumbleCarpetBomb.description: Rumble fires off a group of rockets, creating a wall of flames that damages and slows enemies.

RyzeQWrapper.name: Overload
RyzeQWrapper.description:
Passively, Ryze's other basic abilities reset the cooldown of Overload and charge a rune. When Ryze casts Overload with 2 runes charged, he gains a brief burst of Move Speed.

On cast, Ryze throws a charge of pure energy in a line, dealing damage to the first enemy struck. If the target has Flux on it, Overload deals extra damage and bounces to nearby enemies with Flux.

RyzeW.name: Rune Prison
RyzeW.description: Ryze traps a target in a cage of runes, damaging them and slowing their movement. If the target has Flux on it, they are instead rooted.

RyzeE.name: Spell Flux
RyzeE.description: Ryze releases an orb of pure magical power that damages an enemy and debuffs all nearby enemies. Ryze's spells have additional effects against the debuffed enemy.

RyzeR.name: Realm Warp
RyzeR.description:
Passively, Overload deals even more damage against targets with Flux.

On cast, Ryze creates a portal to a nearby location. After a few seconds, allies standing near the portal are teleported to the target location.

SamiraQ.name: Flair
SamiraQ.description: Samira fires a shot or swings her sword, dealing damage. If cast during Wild Rush, strike all enemies in her path upon completion.

SamiraW.name: Blade Whirl
SamiraW.description: Samira slashes around her, damaging enemies and destroying enemy missiles.

SamiraE.name: Wild Rush
SamiraE.description: Samira dashes through an enemy (including structures), slashing enemies she passes through and gaining Attack Speed. Killing an enemy champion refreshes this ability's cooldown.

SamiraR.name: Inferno Trigger
SamiraR.description: Samira unleashes a torrent of shots from her weapons, wildly shooting all enemies surrounding her.

SejuaniQ.name: Arctic Assault
SejuaniQ.description: Sejuani charges forward, knocking enemies into the air. The charge stops after hitting an enemy champion.

SejuaniW.name: Winter's Wrath
SejuaniW.description: Sejuani swings her mace twice, dealing damage, slowing enemies and applying Frost stacks.

SejuaniE.name: Permafrost
SejuaniE.description: Sejuani freezes and stuns an enemy champion that has maximum Frost stacks.

SejuaniR.name: Glacial Prison
SejuaniR.description: Sejuani throws her bola that freezes and stuns the first champion hit and creates an ice storm that slows other enemies.

SennaQ.name: Piercing Darkness
SennaQ.description: From the twin barrels of her Relic Cannon, Senna fires a unified beam of light and shadow through a target, healing allies and damaging enemies.

SennaW.name: Last Embrace
SennaW.description: Senna sends forth a wave of Black Mist. If it hits an enemy it latches onto them hungrily, rooting them and everything nearby after a brief delay.

SennaE.name: Curse of the Black Mist
SennaE.description: Senna draws the Mist she has stored in her weapon into a storm around her, embracing darkness and becoming a wraith within. Allies who enter the area are camouflaged and also appear as wraiths as the Mist shrouds them. Wraiths gain increased Move Speed, are unselectable, and hide their identities.

SennaR.name: Dawning Shadow
SennaR.description: Senna calls upon the relic stones of fallen Sentinels, splitting her relic cannon into a holy array of shadow and light. She then fires a global beam that shields allies from harm, while damaging enemies caught in the center.

SeraphineQ.name: High Note
SeraphineQ.description: Seraphine deals damage in an area.

SeraphineW.name: Surround Sound
SeraphineW.description: Seraphine Shields and Hastes nearby allies. If she is already Shielded she will Heal nearby allies as well.

SeraphineE.name: Beat Drop
SeraphineE.description: Seraphine deals damage and impairs the movement of enemies in a line.

SeraphineR.name: Encore
SeraphineR.description: Seraphine deals damage and charms enemies hit, refreshing the range with every allied or enemy champion hit.

SettQ.name: Knuckle Down
SettQ.description: Sett's next two attacks deal additional damage based off of the target's max health. Sett also gains Move Speed while moving towards enemy champions.

SettW.name: Haymaker
SettW.description: Sett passively stores damage he takes as Grit. On cast, Sett expends all stored Grit to gain a shield and punch an area, dealing true damage in the center and physical damage on the sides.

SettE.name: Facebreaker
SettE.description: Sett pulls in all enemies on opposite sides of him, dealing damage and stunning them. If enemies were only on one side, they are slowed instead of stunned.

SettR.name: The Show Stopper
SettR.description: Sett carries an enemy champion through the air and slams them into the ground, dealing damage and slowing all enemies near where they land.

Deceive.name: Deceive
Deceive.description:
Shaco becomes Invisible and teleports to target location.

His first attack while Invisible is empowered, dealing bonus damage and critically striking if he attacks from behind.

JackInTheBox.name: Jack In The Box
JackInTheBox.description: Shaco creates a hidden animated Jack-in-the-Box. When triggered, it will fear and attack nearby enemies.

TwoShivPoison.name: Two-Shiv Poison
TwoShivPoison.description: Shaco's Shivs passively poison targets on hit, slowing their Move Speed. He can throw his Shivs to deal damage and poison the target. The thrown Shiv deals bonus damage if the target is below 30% health.

HallucinateFull.name: Hallucinate
HallucinateFull.description: Shaco creates an illusion of himself near him, which can attack nearby enemies (Deals reduced damage to turrets).  Upon death, it explodes, spawning three mini Jack in the Boxes and dealing damage to nearby enemies.

ShenQ.name: Twilight Assault
ShenQ.description: Shen recalls his spirit blade to attack with it, dealing damage based on the target's max health. The attacks are greatly empowered if it collides with an enemy champion, and all collided enemies are slowed while running away from Shen.

ShenW.name: Spirit's Refuge
ShenW.description: Attacks that would hit Shen or his allies near his spirit blade are blocked.

ShenE.name: Shadow Dash
ShenE.description: Shen dashes in a direction, taunting enemies in his path.

ShenR.name: Stand United
ShenR.description: Shen shields target allied champion from incoming damage, and soon after teleports to their location.

ShyvanaDoubleAttack.name: Twin Bite
ShyvanaDoubleAttack.description:
Shyvana strikes twice on her next attack and grants herself Attack Speed for her next attacks. Basic attacks reduce the cooldown of Twin Bite by 0.5 seconds.

Dragon Form: Twin Bite cleaves all units in front of Shyvana.

ShyvanaImmolationAura.name: Burnout
ShyvanaImmolationAura.description:
Shyvana surrounds herself in fire, dealing magic damage per second to nearby enemies and moving faster for 3 seconds, part of this damage is applied again when Shyvana basic attacks an enemy with Burnout active. The Move Speed reduces over the duration of the spell. Basic attacks extend the duration of Burnout.

Dragon Form: Burnout grows in size.

ShyvanaFireball.name: Flame Breath
ShyvanaFireball.description:
Shyvana unleashes a fireball that deals damage to all enemies it encounters and leaves cinders on the target, marking them for 5 seconds. Shyvana's basic attacks on marked targets deal a percentage of their maximum Health as damage on-hit.

Dragon Form: Flame Breath explodes on impact or at target location, dealing bonus damage and scorching the earth for a short duration.

ShyvanaTransformCast.name: Dragon's Descent
ShyvanaTransformCast.description:
Shyvana transforms into a dragon and takes flight to a target location. Enemies along her path take damage and are knocked toward her target location.

Shyvana passively gains Fury per second and gains 2 Fury on basic attack.

PoisonTrail.name: Poison Trail
PoisonTrail.description: Leaves a trail of poison behind Singed, dealing damage to enemies caught in the path.

MegaAdhesive.name: Mega Adhesive
MegaAdhesive.description: Throws a vial of mega adhesive on the ground, slowing and grounding enemies who walk on it.

Fling.name: Fling
Fling.description: Damages target enemy unit and flings them into the air behind Singed. If the target Singed flings lands in his Mega Adhesive, they are also rooted.

InsanityPotion.name: Insanity Potion
InsanityPotion.description: Singed drinks a potent brew of chemicals, granting him increased combat stats, and making his Poison Trail apply Grievous Wounds.

SionQ.name: Decimating Smash
SionQ.description: Sion charges a powerful swing in an area in front of himself that will deal damage to enemies when released. If he charges for enough time, enemies hit by the swing will also be knocked up and stunned.

SionW.name: Soul Furnace
SionW.description: Sion shields himself and can reactivate after 3 seconds to deal Magic Damage to enemies nearby. When Sion kills enemies, he passively gains maximum Health.

SionE.name: Roar of the Slayer
SionE.description: Sion fires a short range shockwave that damages and slows and reduces the Armor of the first enemy hit. If the shockwave hits a minion or monster, it will be knocked back, damaging, slowing, and reducing the Armor of all enemies that it passes through.

SionR.name: Unstoppable Onslaught
SionR.description: Sion charges in a direction, ramping up speed over time. He can steer his charge slightly with the mouse cursor location. When he collides with an enemy he deals damage and knocks them up based on the distance he has charged.

SivirQ.name: Boomerang Blade
SivirQ.description: Sivir hurls her crossblade like a boomerang, dealing damage each way.

SivirW.name: Ricochet
SivirW.description: Sivir's next few basic attacks gain additional attack speed and bounce to nearby targets, dealing reduced damage while bouncing.

SivirE.name: Spell Shield
SivirE.description: Creates a magical barrier that blocks a single enemy ability cast on Sivir. She receives health and a burst of movement speed if a spell is blocked.

SivirR.name: On The Hunt
SivirR.description: Sivir leads her allies in battle, granting them a surge of Move Speed for a period of time. In addition, Sivir's attacks reduce her spell cooldowns.

SkarnerQ.name: Shattered Earth / Upheaval
SkarnerQ.description: Skarner rips a boulder from the earth that empowers his attacks and can be thrown as a powerful projectile.

SkarnerW.name: Seismic Bastion
SkarnerW.description: Skarner gains a shield and creates an earthquake whose shockwave damages and slows foes.

SkarnerE.name: Ixtal's Impact
SkarnerE.description: Skarner charges forward and passes through terrain. If he collides with a champion or large monster, he'll slam them into the next wall he hits to damage and stun them.

SkarnerR.name: Impale
SkarnerR.description: Skarner's tails lash forward to suppress enemy champions. Once suppressed, the victims will be dragged along by Skarner as he moves around.

SmolderQ.name: Super Scorcher Breath
SmolderQ.description: Smolder breathes fire on an enemy. As he gains more stacks, this ability becomes more powerful.

SmolderW.name: Achooo!
SmolderW.description: Smolder lets out an adorable flaming sneeze that explodes when hitting enemy champions.

SmolderE.name: Flap, Flap, Flap
SmolderE.description: Smolder takes flight ignoring terrain and bombarding the lowest health enemy.

SmolderR.name: MMOOOMMMM!
SmolderR.description: Smolder calls his mom to breath fire from above, dealing extra damage and slowing enemies in the center of her fire.

SonaQ.name: Hymn of Valor
SonaQ.description: Sona plays the Hymn of Valor, sends out bolts of sound, dealing magic damage to two nearby enemies, prioritizing champions and monsters. Sona gains a temporary aura that grants allies tagged by the zone bonus damage on their next attack against enemies.

SonaW.name: Aria of Perseverance
SonaW.description: Sona plays the Aria of Perseverance, sending out protective melodies, healing Sona and a nearby wounded ally. Sona gains a temporary aura that grants allies tagged by the zone a temporary shield.

SonaE.name: Song of Celerity
SonaE.description: Sona plays the Song of Celerity, granting nearby allies bonus Move Speed. Sona gains a temporary aura that grants allied champions tagged by the zone bonus Move Speed.

SonaR.name: Crescendo
SonaR.description: Sona plays her ultimate chord, stunning enemy champions and forcing them to dance and dealing magic damage to them.

SorakaQ.name: Starcall
SorakaQ.description: A star falls from the sky at the target location dealing magic damage and slowing enemies. If an enemy champion is hit by Starcall, Soraka recovers Health.

SorakaW.name: Astral Infusion
SorakaW.description: Soraka sacrifices a portion of her own health to heal another friendly champion.

SorakaE.name: Equinox
SorakaE.description: Creates a zone at a location that silences all enemies inside. When the zone expires, all enemies still inside are rooted.

SorakaR.name: Wish
SorakaR.description: Soraka fills her allies with hope, instantly restoring health to herself and all allied champions.

SwainQ.name: Death's Hand
SwainQ.description: Swain unleashes several bolts of eldritch power that pierce through enemies. Enemies hit take more damage for each bolt they are struck by.

SwainW.name: Vision of Empire
SwainW.description: Swain opens a demon eye that deals damage and slows enemies. Champions hit are revealed and also grant Swain a Soul Fragment.

SwainE.name: Nevermove
SwainE.description: Swain launches a wave of demonic power forward. It then returns to Swain and roots enemies it hits. Swain can then choose to pull all rooted champions closer. This ability has a shorter cooldown during Demonic Ascension.

SwainR.name: Demonic Ascension
SwainR.description: Swain transforms into a demon and drains health from nearby enemy champions, minions, and neutral monsters. Swain can cast Demonflare to decimate and slow nearby enemies with a nova of soulfire. This form is indefinite as long as Swain drains enemy champions.

SylasQ.name: Chain Lash
SylasQ.description:
Sylas lashes his chains out, intersecting at his targeted location dealing damage to and slowing enemies.

After a delay, magical energy explodes from the intersection point dealing damage.

SylasW.name: Kingslayer
SylasW.description: Sylas lunges at an enemy with magical force dealing damage and healing himself against enemy champions.

SylasE.name: Abscond / Abduct
SylasE.description: Sylas dashes to a location. Sylas can recast the ability to throw his chains out, pulling himself to an enemy he hits.

SylasR.name: Hijack
SylasR.description: Sylas steals the enemy's ultimate ability and can cast it freely.

SyndraQ.name: Dark Sphere
SyndraQ.description: Syndra conjures a Dark Sphere dealing magic damage. The sphere remains and can be manipulated by her other powers.

SyndraW.name: Force of Will
SyndraW.description: Syndra picks up and throws a Dark Sphere or enemy minion dealing magic damage and slowing the Move Speed of enemies.

SyndraE.name: Scatter the Weak
SyndraE.description: Syndra knocks enemies and Dark Spheres back dealing magic damage. Enemies hit by Dark Spheres become stunned.

SyndraR.name: Unleashed Power
SyndraR.description: Syndra bombards an enemy Champion with all of her Dark Spheres.

TahmKenchQ.name: Tongue Lash
TahmKenchQ.description:
Tahm Kench lashes out with his tongue, damaging and slowing the first unit hit and healing himself if he strikes an enemy champion.

Applies a stack of An Acquired Taste to enemy champions. If the champion already has 3 stacks of An Acquired Taste, they are stunned and the stacks are consumed.

TahmKenchW.name: Abyssal Dive
TahmKenchW.description: Dive down and then re-appear at target location, damaging and knocking up all enemies in an area.

TahmKenchE.name: Thick Skin
TahmKenchE.description:
Passive: Tahm Kench stores a percent of the damage he takes and heals based on it while out of combat.

Active: Convert all stored damage into a temporary shield.

TahmKenchRWrapper.name: Devour
TahmKenchRWrapper.description: Tahm Kench devours a champion for a few seconds, dealing magic damage if they are an enemy, or shielding them if they are an ally.

TaliyahQ.name: Threaded Volley
TaliyahQ.description: Taliyah throws a volley of rocks in a target direction, moving freely as she casts. This creates Worked Ground below her. If Taliyah casts Threaded Volley on Worked Ground, she consumes the ground to throw a stronger boulder that slows enemies.

TaliyahWVC.name: Seismic Shove
TaliyahWVC.description: Taliyah causes an area of ground to erupt and throws enemies within it in a direction of her choosing.

TaliyahE.name: Unraveled Earth
TaliyahE.description: Taliyah creates a slowing minefield. If enemies dash through it or are knocked through it, the mines explode and stun them.

TaliyahR.name: Weaver's Wall
TaliyahR.description: Taliyah creates a very long wall and then surfs it.

TalonQ.name: Noxian Diplomacy
TalonQ.description: Talon stabs the target unit. If they are within melee range, this attack deals critical damage. If they are outside melee range, Talon will leap at his target before stabbing them. Talon refunds some health and cooldown if this ability kills the target.

TalonW.name: Rake
TalonW.description: Talon sends out a volley of daggers that then return back to him, dealing physical damage every time it passes through an enemy. The returning blades deal bonus damage and slow units hit.

TalonE.name: Assassin's Path
TalonE.description: Talon vaults over any terrain or structure, up to a max distance. This ability has a low cooldown, but puts the used terrain on a long cooldown.

TalonR.name: Shadow Assault
TalonR.description: Talon disperses a ring of blades and becomes Invisible while gaining additional Move Speed. When Talon emerges from Invisibility, the blades converge on his location. Each time the blades move, Shadow Assault deals physical damage to enemies hit by at least one blade.

TaricQ.name: Starlight's Touch
TaricQ.description: Heals nearby allied champions based on charges stored. Bravado-empowered attacks grant a charge of Starlight's Touch.

TaricW.name: Bastion
TaricW.description:
Passively increase the Armor of Taric and any allied champion with Bastion.

Actively shields an ally and grants them Bastion for as long as they remain near Taric. Taric's spells also cast off the ally with Bastion.

TaricE.name: Dazzle
TaricE.description: Taric readies a beam of starlight that, after a brief delay, deals magic damage and stuns enemies.

TaricR.name: Cosmic Radiance
TaricR.description: Pulses cosmic energy onto nearby allied champions after a delay, making them invulnerable for a short duration.

TeemoQ.name: Blinding Dart
TeemoQ.description: Obscures an enemy's vision with a powerful venom, dealing damage to the target unit and blinding it for the duration.

TeemoW.name: Move Quick
TeemoW.description: Teemo scampers around, passively increasing his Move Speed until he is struck by an enemy champion or turret. Teemo can sprint to gain bonus Move Speed that isn't stopped by being struck for a short time.

TeemoE.name: Toxic Shot
TeemoE.description: Each of Teemo's attacks will poison the target, dealing damage on impact and each second after for 4 seconds.

TeemoR.name: Noxious Trap
TeemoR.description: Teemo throws an explosive poisonous trap using one of the mushrooms stored in his pack. If an enemy steps on the trap, it will release a poisonous cloud, slowing enemies and damaging them over time. If Teemo throws a mushroom onto another mushroom it will bounce, gaining additional range.

ThreshQ.name: Death Sentence
ThreshQ.description: Thresh binds an enemy in chains and pulls them toward him. Activating this ability a second time pulls Thresh to the enemy.

ThreshW.name: Dark Passage
ThreshW.description: Thresh throws out a lantern that shields nearby allied Champions from damage. Allies can click the lantern to dash to Thresh.

ThreshE.name: Flay
ThreshE.description: Thresh's attacks wind up, dealing more damage the longer he waits between attacks. When activated, Thresh sweeps his chain, knocking all enemies hit in the direction of the blow.

ThreshRPenta.name: The Box
ThreshRPenta.description: A prison of walls that slow and deal damage if broken.

TristanaQ.name: Rapid Fire
TristanaQ.description: Tristana fires her weapon rapidly, increasing her Attack Speed for a short time.

TristanaW.name: Rocket Jump
TristanaW.description: Tristana fires at the ground to propel her to a distant location, dealing damage and slowing surrounding units for a brief period where she lands.

TristanaE.name: Explosive Charge
TristanaE.description: When Tristana kills a unit, her cannonballs burst into shrapnel, dealing damage to surrounding enemies. Can be activated to place a bomb on a target enemy that explodes after a short duration dealing damage to surrounding units.

TristanaR.name: Buster Shot
TristanaR.description: Tristana loads a massive cannonball into her weapon and fires it at an enemy unit. This deals Magic Damage and knocks the target back. If the target is carrying the Explosive Charge bomb, the bomb detonation radius is doubled.

TrundleTrollSmash.name: Chomp
TrundleTrollSmash.description: Trundle bites his opponent, dealing damage, briefly slowing and sapping some of their Attack Damage.

trundledesecrate.name: Frozen Domain
trundledesecrate.description: Trundle turns target location into his domain, gaining Attack Speed, Move Speed, and increased healing from all sources while on it.

TrundleCircle.name: Pillar of Ice
TrundleCircle.description: Trundle creates an ice pillar at target location, becoming impassable terrain and slowing all nearby enemy units.

TrundlePain.name: Subjugate
TrundlePain.description: Trundle immediately steals a percent of his target's Health, Armor and Magic Resistance. Over the next 4 seconds the amount of Health, Armor, and Magic Resistance stolen is doubled.

TryndamereQ.name: Bloodlust
TryndamereQ.description: Tryndamere thrives on the thrills of combat, increasing his Attack Damage as he is more and more wounded. He can cast Bloodlust to consume his Fury and heal himself.

TryndamereW.name: Mocking Shout
TryndamereW.description: Tryndamere lets out an insulting cry, decreasing surrounding champions' Attack Damage. Enemies with their backs turned to Tryndamere also have their Move Speed reduced.

TryndamereE.name: Spinning Slash
TryndamereE.description: Tryndamere slices toward a target unit, dealing damage to enemies in his path.

UndyingRage.name: Undying Rage
UndyingRage.description: Tryndamere's lust for battle becomes so strong that he is unable to die, no matter how wounded he becomes.

WildCards.name: Wild Cards
WildCards.description: Twisted Fate throws three cards, dealing damage to each enemy unit they pass through.

PickACard.name: Pick a Card
PickACard.description: Twisted Fate chooses a magic card from his deck, and uses that for his next attack, causing bonus effects.

CardmasterStack.name: Stacked Deck
CardmasterStack.description: Every 4 attacks, Twisted Fate deals bonus damage. In addition, his Attack Speed is increased.

Destiny.name: Destiny
Destiny.description: Twisted Fate predicts the fortunes of his foes, revealing all enemy champions and enabling the use of Gate, which teleports Twisted Fate to any target location in 1.5 seconds.

TwitchHideInShadows.name: Ambush
TwitchHideInShadows.description:
Twitch becomes Camouflaged for a short duration and gains Move Speed. When leaving Camouflage, Twitch gains Attack Speed for a short duration.

When an enemy champion with Deadly Venom dies, Ambush's cooldown is reset.

TwitchVenomCask.name: Venom Cask
TwitchVenomCask.description: Twitch hurls a cask of venom that explodes in an area, slowing targets and applying deadly venom to the target.

TwitchExpunge.name: Contaminate
TwitchExpunge.description: Twitch wreaks further havoc on poisoned enemies with a blast of his vile diseases.

TwitchFullAutomatic.name: Spray and Pray
TwitchFullAutomatic.description: Twitch unleashes the full power of his crossbow, shooting bolts over a great distance that pierce all enemies caught in their path.

UdyrQ.name: Wilding Claw
UdyrQ.description: Udyr gains attack speed and his next two attacks deal bonus physical damage. Recast: Gain even more attack speed, and the next two attacks call lightning to strike the target.

UdyrW.name: Iron Mantle
UdyrW.description: Udyr gains a shield and his next two attacks heal him. Recast: Gain an even bigger shield and heal based on max health over the next couple seconds.

UdyrE.name: Blazing Stampede
UdyrE.description: Udyr gains movement speed and his first attack against each target will Stun them. Recast: Gain even more movement speed and immunity to immobilizing effects for a couple seconds.

UdyrR.name: Wingborne Storm
UdyrR.description: Udyr surrounds himself in a glacial storm, damaging and slowing nearby enemies. Recast: Empower and unleash the storm, causing it to track enemies and deal additional damage.

UrgotQ.name: Corrosive Charge
UrgotQ.description: Fires an explosive charge at the target location, dealing physical damage and slowing enemies caught in the explosion.

UrgotW.name: Purge
UrgotW.description: Urgot slows himself while he unloads his weapon on nearby enemies. Prioritizes enemy champions Urgot has recently struck with other abilities and triggers Echoing Flames.

UrgotE.name: Disdain
UrgotE.description: Urgot charges in a direction, shielding himself and trampling non-champion enemies. If he catches an enemy champion, he will stop and hurl them out of his way.

UrgotR.name: Fear Beyond Death
UrgotR.description: Urgot fires a chem-drill that impales the first enemy champion hit. If that champion falls below a health threshold, Urgot judges them weak and can execute them.

VarusQ.name: Piercing Arrow
VarusQ.description: Varus readies and then fires a powerful shot that gains extra range and damage the longer he spends preparing to fire.

VarusW.name: Blighted Quiver
VarusW.description: Passive: Varus' basic attacks deal bonus magic damage and apply Blight. Varus' other abilities detonate Blight, dealing magic damage based on the target's maximum Health. Active: Varus empowers his next Piercing Arrow.

VarusE.name: Hail of Arrows
VarusE.description: Varus fires a hail of arrows that deal physical damage and desecrate the ground. Desecrated ground slows enemies' Move Speed and reduces their self healing and regeneration.

VarusR.name: Chain of Corruption
VarusR.description: Varus flings out a damaging tendril of corruption that immobilizes the first enemy champion hit and then spreads towards nearby uninfected champions, immobilizing them too on contact.

VayneTumble.name: Tumble
VayneTumble.description: Vayne tumbles, maneuvering to carefully place her next shot. Her next attack deals bonus damage.

VayneSilveredBolts.name: Silver Bolts
VayneSilveredBolts.description: Vayne tips her bolts with a rare metal, toxic to evil things. The third consecutive attack or ability against the same target deals a percentage of the target's max health as bonus true damage.

VayneCondemn.name: Condemn
VayneCondemn.description: Vayne draws a heavy crossbow from her back, and fires a huge bolt at her target, knocking them back and dealing damage. If they collide with terrain, they are impaled, dealing bonus damage and stunning them.

VayneInquisition.name: Final Hour
VayneInquisition.description: Readying herself for an epic confrontation, Vayne gains increased Attack Damage, Invisibility during Tumble, reduced Tumble cooldown, and more bonus Move Speed from Night Hunter

VeigarBalefulStrike.name: Baleful Strike
VeigarBalefulStrike.description: Veigar unleashes a bolt of dark energy that deals magic damage to the first two enemies hit. Units killed by this bolt grant Veigar some ability power permanently.

VeigarDarkMatter.name: Dark Matter
VeigarDarkMatter.description: Veigar calls a great mass of dark matter to fall from the sky to the target location, dealing magic damage when it lands. Stacks of Phenomenal Evil reduce Dark Matter's cooldown.

VeigarEventHorizon.name: Event Horizon
VeigarEventHorizon.description: Veigar twists the edges of space, creating a cage that Stuns enemies that pass through.

VeigarR.name: Primordial Burst
VeigarR.description: Blasts target enemy champion, dealing a large amount of magic damage, increasing based on the target's missing health.

VelkozQ.name: Plasma Fission
VelkozQ.description: Vel'Koz shoots a bolt of plasma that splits in two on reactivation or upon hitting an enemy. The bolt slows and damages on hit.

VelkozW.name: Void Rift
VelkozW.description: Vel'Koz opens a rift to the void that deals an initial burst of damage, then explodes for a second burst of damage after a delay.

VelkozE.name: Tectonic Disruption
VelkozE.description: Vel'Koz causes an area to explode, knocking up enemies, and knocking close enemies slightly away.

VelkozR.name: Life Form Disintegration Ray
VelkozR.description: Vel'Koz unleashes a channelled beam that follows the cursor for 2.5 seconds that deals magic damage. Organic Deconstruction Researches enemy champions causing them to take true damage instead.

VexQ.name: Mistral Bolt
VexQ.description: Launch a damaging missile that accelerates mid-flight.

VexW.name: Personal Space
VexW.description: Gain a shield and damage nearby enemies.

VexE.name: Looming Darkness
VexE.description: Summon a damaging and slowing zone that applies Gloom to enemies.

VexR.name: Shadow Surge
VexR.description: Fire a missile that marks an enemy champion.  Recast to dash to them and deal damage.

ViQ.name: Vault Breaker
ViQ.description: Vi charges her gauntlets and unleashes a vault shattering punch, carrying her forward. Enemies she hits are knocked back and receive a stack of Denting Blows.

ViW.name: Denting Blows
ViW.description: Vi's punches break her opponent's Armor, dealing bonus damage and granting her Attack Speed.

ViE.name: Relentless Force
ViE.description: Vi's next attack blasts through her target, dealing damage to enemies behind it.

ViR.name: Cease and Desist
ViR.description: Vi runs down an enemy, knocking aside anyone in the way. When she reaches her target she knocks it into the air, jumps after it, and slams it back into the ground.

ViegoQ.name: Blade of the Ruined King
ViegoQ.description:
Viego's spectral blade passively deals bonus percent current Health damage On-Hit and strikes twice vs. enemies he recently hit with an Ability, stealing Health.

Viego can activate this Ability to thrust his zweihander forward, impaling enemies in front of him.

ViegoW.name: Spectral Maw
ViegoW.description: Viego charges up before dashing forward, releasing a ball of concentrated Black Mist that stuns the first enemy hit.

ViegoE.name: Harrowed Path
ViegoE.description: Viego commands the Black Mist to haunt and surround a piece of terrain. Viego can hide in the Mist as a wraith, gaining camouflage, Move Speed, and Attack Speed.

ViegoR.name: Heartbreaker
ViegoR.description: Viego teleports to a nearby location and executes an enemy champion on arrival, piercing their heart and causing a destructive shockwave around them that knocks away their allies.

ViktorQ.name: Siphon Power
ViktorQ.description:
Viktor blasts an enemy unit with magic damage, which grants him a shield and empowers his next basic attack.

Augment: Siphon Power's shield is increased by 60% and Viktor gains bonus move speed after casting the Ability.

ViktorW.name: Gravity Field
ViktorW.description:
Viktor conjures a heavy gravitational field that slows enemies caught within its radius. Enemies who stay in the field for too long become stunned.

Augment: Viktor's spells apply a slow to enemies.

ViktorE.name: Hextech Ray
ViktorE.description:
Viktor uses his biomechanical arm to fire a Hextech Ray that cuts across the field in a line, dealing damage to all enemies in its path.

Augment: An explosion follows in the Hextech Ray's wake, dealing magic damage.

ViktorR.name: Arcane Storm
ViktorR.description:
Viktor conjures an Arcane Storm on the field, dealing magic damage and interrupting enemy channels. The storm periodically does magic damage to all nearby enemies and can be redirected by Viktor.

Augment: The Arcane Storm moves 25% faster, and whenever champions die after taking damage from it, the storm grows and increases in its duration.

VladimirQ.name: Transfusion
VladimirQ.description: Vladimir steals life from the target enemy. When Vladimir's resource is full, Transfusion will benefit from massively increased damage and healing for a brief time.

VladimirSanguinePool.name: Sanguine Pool
VladimirSanguinePool.description: Vladimir sinks into a pool of blood, becoming untargetable for 2 seconds. Additionally, enemies on the pool are slowed and Vladimir siphons life from them.

VladimirE.name: Tides of Blood
VladimirE.description: Vladimir pays his own health to charge up a reservoir of blood which, when released, deals damage in the area around him but can be blocked by enemy units.

VladimirHemoplague.name: Hemoplague
VladimirHemoplague.description: Vladimir infects an area with a virulent plague. Affected enemies take increased damage for the duration. After a few seconds, Hemoplague deals magic damage to infected enemies and heals Vladimir for each enemy Champion hit.

VolibearQ.name: Thundering Smash
VolibearQ.description: Volibear gains speed towards enemies, <status>Stunning</status> and damaging the first one he Attacks.

VolibearW.name: Frenzied Maul
VolibearW.description: Volibear damages an enemy, applying on-hit effects and marking them.  Casting this ability again on the same target deals bonus damage and Heals Volibear.

VolibearE.name: Sky Splitter
VolibearE.description: Volibear summons a lightning bolt at a location, dealing damage and Slowing enemies while granting Volibear a Shield if he's inside the blast radius.

VolibearR.name: Stormbringer
VolibearR.description: Volibear leaps to a target location, Slowing and damaging enemies beneath him while gaining bonus Health.  Enemy towers near his landing location become temporarily disabled.

WarwickQ.name: Jaws of the Beast
WarwickQ.description: Warwick lunges forward and bites his target, dealing damage based on their maximum health and healing for damage dealt.

WarwickW.name: Blood Hunt
WarwickW.description: Warwick senses enemies below 50% health, gaining Move Speed toward and attack speed against them. When they fall below 25% health, he frenzies and these bonuses triple.

WarwickE.name: Primal Howl
WarwickE.description: Warwick gains damage reduction for 2.5 seconds. At the end, or if re-activated, he howls, causing nearby enemies to flee for 1 second.

WarwickR.name: Infinite Duress
WarwickR.description: Warwick leaps in a direction (scaling with his bonus Move Speed), suppressing the first champion he collides with for 1.5 seconds.

XayahQ.name: Double Daggers
XayahQ.description: Xayah throws two damaging daggers that also drop Feathers she can recall.

XayahW.name: Deadly Plumage
XayahW.description: Xayah creates a storm of blades that increase her Attack Speed and damage while also granting her Move Speed if she attacks a champion.

XayahE.name: Bladecaller
XayahE.description: Xayah calls back all her dropped Feathers dealing damage and rooting enemies.

XayahR.name: Featherstorm
XayahR.description: Xayah leaps into the air becoming untargetable and throwing out a fan of daggers, dropping Feathers she can recall.

XerathArcanopulseChargeUp.name: Arcanopulse
XerathArcanopulseChargeUp.description: Fires a long-range beam of energy, dealing magic damage to all targets hit.

XerathArcaneBarrage2.name: Eye of Destruction
XerathArcaneBarrage2.description: Calls down a barrage of arcane energy, slowing and dealing magic damage to all enemies in an area. Targets in the middle receive additional damage and a stronger slow.

XerathMageSpear.name: Shocking Orb
XerathMageSpear.description: Deals magic damage to an enemy and stuns them.

XerathLocusOfPower2.name: Rite of the Arcane
XerathLocusOfPower2.description: Xerath immobilizes himself and gains numerous long-range barrages.

XinZhaoQ.name: Three Talon Strike
XinZhaoQ.description: Xin Zhao's next 3 standard attacks deal increased damage with the third attack knocking an opponent into the air.

XinZhaoW.name: Wind Becomes Lightning
XinZhaoW.description: Xin Zhao slashes in front of himself with his spear, then thrusts it forward, slowing affected enemies and marking them as Challenged.

XinZhaoE.name: Audacious Charge
XinZhaoE.description: Xin Zhao charges to an enemy, gaining increased Attack Speed and dealing damage to all enemies in the area, slowing them briefly. Audacious Charge gains increased range against Challenged targets.

XinZhaoR.name: Crescent Guard
XinZhaoR.description: Xin Zhao challenges an enemy he damaged recently. Xin Zhao deals damage to nearby enemies based on their current Health and knocks non-challenged targets back, becoming impervious to damage dealt by champions outside of the circle created.

YasuoQ1Wrapper.name: Steel Tempest
YasuoQ1Wrapper.description:
Thrusts forward, damaging all enemies in a line.

On hit, grants a stack of Gathering Storm for a few seconds. At 2 stacks, Steel Tempest fires a whirlwind that knocks Airborne.

Steel Tempest is treated as a basic attack and scales with all the same things.

YasuoW.name: Wind Wall
YasuoW.description: Creates a moving wall that blocks all enemy projectiles for 4 seconds.

YasuoE.name: Sweeping Blade
YasuoE.description:
Dashes through target enemy, dealing magic damage. Each cast increases subsequent dash's damage, up to a max amount.

Cannot be re-cast on the same enemy for a few seconds.

If Steel Tempest is cast while dashing, it will strike as a circle.

YasuoR.name: Last Breath
YasuoR.description:
Blinks to an Airborne enemy champion, dealing physical damage and holding all Airborne enemies in the area in the air. Grants maximum Flow but resets all stacks of Gathering Storm.

For a moderate time afterwards, Yasuo's critical strikes gain significant Bonus Armor Penetration.

YoneQ.name: Mortal Steel
YoneQ.description:
Thrusts forward, damaging all enemies in a line.

On hit, grants a stack of Gathering Storm for a few seconds. At 2 stacks, Mortal Steel dashes Yone forward with a gust of wind knocking enemies Airborne.

YoneW.name: Spirit Cleave
YoneW.description:
Cleaves forward, damaging all enemies in a cone. Grants a shield to Yone, the value is increased by the number of champions hit by the swipe.

Spirit Cleave's cooldown and cast time scale with attack speed.

YoneE.name: Soul Unbound
YoneE.description: Yone's spirit leaves his body behind, gaining Move Speed. When this ability ends, Yone's spirit is forced back to his body and he repeats a portion of the damage he dealt as a spirit.

YoneR.name: Fate Sealed
YoneR.description: Yone blinks behind the last champion in a line with a slash so powerful it pulls all enemies hit towards him.

YorickQ.name: Last Rites
YorickQ.description: Yorick deals bonus damage on his next attack and heals himself. If the target is a champion or large monster or if the target dies, a grave will be dug.

YorickW.name: Dark Procession
YorickW.description: Yorick summons a destructible wall at target location that will block enemy movement.

YorickE.name: Mourning Mist
YorickE.description: Yorick throws a globule of Black Mist that reduces armor, damages, slows and marks enemies. Summoned units gain move speed when moving towards marked targets.

YorickR.name: Eulogy of the Isles
YorickR.description: Yorick summons the Maiden of the Mist that causes Yorick's attacks against the Maiden's target to deal bonus damage. The Maiden will also automatically raise Walkers from dead enemies.

YunaraQ.name: Cultivation of Spirit
YunaraQ.description: Yunara gains Attack Speed, bonus damage On-Hit, and her Attacks spread to nearby enemies.

YunaraW.name: Arc of Judgment | Arc of Ruin
YunaraW.description: Yunara fires a spinning prayer bead that deals damage and slows enemies. While in her Transcendent State she instead fires off a laser that deals damage and slows enemies.

YunaraE.name: Kanmei's Steps | Untouchable Shadow
YunaraE.description: Yunara gains decaying movement speed and becomes Ghosted. While in her Transcendent State she instead dashes in a direction.

YunaraR.name: Transcend One's Self
YunaraR.description: Yunara enters a Transcendent State that upgrades her basic Abilities.

YuumiQ.name: Prowling Projectile
YuumiQ.description:
Yuumi fires a missile, dealing damage and slowing first target hit. It deals bonus damage and an enchanced slow if it takes at least 1.35 seconds to get to its target. While on her Best Friend, the slow is always enhanced and grants bonus On-Hit damage to her ally.

While Attached, the missile can be controlled with your cursor for a brief period.

YuumiW.name: You and Me!
YuumiW.description: Yuumi dashes to a target ally, becoming untargetable from everything except turrets. While on her Best Friend, she gains Heal & Shield Power and grants her Ally On-Hit healing.

YuumiE.name: Zoomies
YuumiE.description: Shields Yuumi and boosts Move Speed and Attack Speed. If she's attached, she passes it to her ally instead.

YuumiR.name: Final Chapter
YuumiR.description: Yuumi channels five waves that damage enemies and heal allies. Yuumi can move, attach, and cast Zoomies! while channeling. While on her Best Friend, this spell also follows her mouse.

ZacQ.name: Stretching Strikes
ZacQ.description: Zac stretches an arm, grabbing an enemy. Attacking a different enemy will cause him to throw both targets towards each other.

ZacW.name: Unstable Matter
ZacW.description: Zac explodes outward towards nearby enemies, dealing a percentage of their maximum health as magic damage.

ZacE.name: Elastic Slingshot
ZacE.description: Zac attaches his arms to the ground and stretches back, launching himself forward.

ZacR.name: Let's Bounce!
ZacR.description: Zac bounces four times, knocking up enemies hit and slowing them.

ZedQ.name: Razor Shuriken
ZedQ.description:
Zed and his shadows throw their shurikens.

Each shuriken deals damage to every enemy hit.

ZedW.name: Living Shadow
ZedW.description:
Passive: Zed gains energy whenever he and his shadows strike an enemy with the same ability. Energy can only be gained once per cast ability.

Active: Zed's shadow dashes forward, remaining in place for a few seconds. Reactivating Living Shadow will cause Zed to switch positions with this shadow.

ZedE.name: Shadow Slash
ZedE.description: Zed and his Shadows slash, dealing damage to nearby enemies. Enemies hit by a Shadow's slash are slowed.

ZedR.name: Death Mark
ZedR.description: Zed becomes untargetable and dashes to an enemy champion, marking them. After 3 seconds the mark triggers, repeating a portion of all the damage Zed dealt to the target while they were marked.

ZeriQ.name: Burst Fire
ZeriQ.description: Burst Fire shoots a burst of 7 rounds that deal attack damage to the first enemy hit. This Ability is treated as an Attack.

ZeriW.name: Ultrashock Laser
ZeriW.description: Zeri fires an electric pulse that slows and damages the first enemy hit. If the pulse hits a wall it expands into a long range laser.

ZeriE.name: Spark Surge
ZeriE.description: Zeri dashes a short distance and energizes her next 3 shots of Burst Fire, causing them to pierce through enemies. She will vault and grind over any terrain she touches.

ZeriR.name: Lightning Crash
ZeriR.description: Zeri discharges a nova of electricity and overcharges herself, gaining increased damage and stacking Move Speed that refreshes and gets stronger every time she hits an enemy champion. While overcharged, Burst fire becomes a faster triple shot that chains lightning between enemies.

ZiggsQ.name: Bouncing Bomb
ZiggsQ.description: Ziggs throws a bouncing bomb that deals magic damage.

ZiggsW.name: Satchel Charge
ZiggsW.description:
Ziggs flings an explosive charge that detonates after a delay, or when this ability is activated again. The explosion deals magic damage to enemies, knocking them away. Ziggs is also knocked away, but takes no damage.

Ziggs can use the Satchel to hexplode vulnerable enemy turrets.

ZiggsE.name: Hexplosive Minefield
ZiggsE.description: Ziggs scatters proximity mines that detonate on enemy contact, dealing magic damage and slowing. Successive mine detonations on the same target deal reduced damage.

ZiggsR.name: Mega Inferno Bomb
ZiggsR.description: Ziggs deploys his ultimate creation, the Mega Inferno Bomb, hurling it an enormous distance. Enemies in the primary blast zone take more damage than those farther away.

ZileanQ.name: Time Bomb
ZileanQ.description: Tosses a bomb to target area that sticks to units that come near it (prioritizes Champions). It detonates after 3 seconds, dealing area of effect damage. If a Time Bomb is detonated early by another Time Bomb, it also stuns enemies.

ZileanW.name: Rewind
ZileanW.description: Zilean can prepare himself for future confrontations, reducing the cooldowns of his other basic abilities.

TimeWarp.name: Time Warp
TimeWarp.description: Zilean bends time around any unit, decreasing an enemy's Move Speed or increasing an ally's Move Speed for a short time.

ChronoShift.name: Chronoshift
ChronoShift.description: Zilean places a protective time rune on an allied champion, teleporting the champion back in time if they take lethal damage.

ZoeQ.name: Paddle Star!
ZoeQ.description: Zoe fires a missile that she can redirect in flight. Deals more damage the longer it flies in a straight line.

ZoeW.name: Spell Thief
ZoeW.description: Zoe can pick up the remnants of enemy summoner spell and active item casts and cast them once herself. Whenever she casts a summoner spell, she gains 3 missiles that fire at the nearest target.

ZoeE.name: Sleepy Trouble Bubble
ZoeE.description: Causes the target to become drowsy, then fall asleep. While asleep, the target's Magic Resist is reduced. The first source of damage that breaks the sleep is doubled, up to a cap.

ZoeR.name: Portal Jump
ZoeR.description: Blink to a nearby position for 1 second. Then blink back.

ZyraQ.name: Deadly Spines
ZyraQ.description: Thick vines spread through the ground and explode into spines, dealing magic damage to enemies within the area. If cast near a seed, Deadly Spines grows a Thorn Spitter plant, which fires at enemies from afar.

ZyraW.name: Rampant Growth
ZyraW.description: Zyra plants a seed, lasting up to 60 seconds. Deadly Spines and Grasping Roots cast near seeds will turn them into plants who fight for Zyra. Zyra can store multiple seeds at once, and killing enemies reduces Rampant Growth's recharge time.

ZyraE.name: Grasping Roots
ZyraE.description: Zyra sends forth vines through the ground to ensnare her target, dealing damage and rooting enemies they come across. If cast near a seed, Grasping Roots grows a Vine Lasher, whose short range attacks reduce enemy Move Speed.

ZyraR.name: Stranglethorns
ZyraR.description: Zyra summons a twisted thicket at her target location, dealing damage to enemies as it expands and knocking them airborne as it contracts. Plants within the thicket are enraged.
